ateNash-interview-featured-photo.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="凯特·纳什（Kate Nash），软戏的劳里·文森特（Laurie Vincent）和艾萨克·霍尔曼（Isaac Holman）以及制片人乔利昂·托马斯（Jolyon Thomas）" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayKateNash-interview-featured-photo.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayKateNash-interview-featured-photo-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayKateNash-interview-featured-photo-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayKateNash-interview-featured-photo-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayKateNash-interview-featured-photo-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayKateNash-interview-featured-photo-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/soft-play">Soft Play</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/kate-nash">Kate Nash</a>已经与<em>NME</em>谈到了他们的合作新单曲“ Slushy”，并反映了音乐行业的“模型被打破”。听这首歌，并阅读下面的完整采访。</p><p>该曲目将出现在Tunbridge Wells Punk Duo的扩展版本上，第三张专辑<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/soft-play-interview-heavy-jelly-chart-interview-eminem-glass-animals-robbie-williams-3778074">“ Heavy Jelly”</a> （去年夏天，其原件都出现了。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kate-nash-interview-butts-for-tour-buses-onlyfans-music-industry-help-lottery-winners-future-3822003">凯特·纳什（Kate Nash），仅在彩票赢家和拯救音乐行业：“主要唱片公司很害怕 - 他们应该是”</a></strong></li></ul><p>乐队的吉他手Laurie Vincent告诉<em>NME</em> ，该项目的标题为“沉重的果冻”，将从LP会议上拍出六首新曲目，这些曲目“对唱片来说太柔软了，但太好了，无法刮擦”。 “ Slushy”的嬉戏二重奏是Nash第二次与Soft Play歌手Isaac Holman一起第二次与他的2023年<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/slaves-isaac-holman-announces-debut-album-for-solo-project-baby-dave-and-shares-new-single-29-3192335">婴儿Dave</a> Solo歌曲<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DldPycd_0O8" target="_blank" rel="noopener">“ Shiteobia”</a>的合作之后。</p><p>纳什（Nash）最近通过<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kate-nash-defends-her-butts-for-tour-buses-onlyfans-campaign-women-being-in-control-of-their-bodies-is-vital-3815393">与成人内容创建者网站仅加入了她的“公共汽车的屁股”激励措施</a>，成为头条新闻，在那里她一直在使用该平台来突出艺术家巡回演出的越来越高。</p><p>文森特与纳什（Nash）一起谈到他们为他们提供巡回工作的财务状况而奋斗时，Vincent向<em>NME</em>透露，由于涉及不切实际的费用，Soft Play最近放弃了欧洲巡回演出的计划。</p><p>他说：“保证金高达近60,000英镑，在（所有费用）之后，我们将最多赚2,000英镑。” “他妈的点是什么？我们正在玩体面的场地，并获得了真正的保证，那么其他人怎么做？我们之所以受到特权，是因为我们能够以我们的英国收入来维持职业，但是有人会如何到达那里？我觉得我们是我们最后一支乐队的时代之一。”</p><p> Check out our full interview below where Soft Play and Nash discuss &#39;Slushy&#39;, how they are similar as artists, why the music industry needs to change, and recall a “bizarre” encounter with <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/robbie-williams">Robbie Williams</a> and Danny Dyer. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Slushy (feat. Kate Nash)" width="696" height="522" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0fPR7BqtTH0?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> <strong>NME: Hi everyone. Kate and Isaac, you already worked together previously on Isaac&#39;s solo project Baby Dave – how far back does the friendship go?</strong></p><p> <strong>Nash:</strong> “When you guys were first popping off, I&#39;d already left the UK by that point so we never ran into each other on the festival circuit, but I obviously knew who you were. In the pandemic, I was listening to your first Baby Dave record and I reached out &#39;cause I loved it so much, and we just started chatting.”</p><p> <strong>Were you old-school Kate Nash fans?</strong></p><p> <strong>Vincent:</strong> “I still listen to &#39;Foundations&#39; and all those old songs in the car with my kids on the school run. Kate Nash is a British indie institution!”</p><p> <strong>What do you think &#39;Slushy&#39; says about your similarities as artists?</strong></p><p> <strong>Nash:</strong> “Both of us, as lyricists and artists, are people that use our environments and where we&#39;re from to tell stories.”</p><p> <strong>Vincent:</strong> “It&#39;s the social observations, like the &#39; <em>cheese on toast</em> &#39; lyric in [Kate&#39;s 2007 track] &#39;Merry Happy&#39;. It&#39;s the same with Isaac: he brings mundane objects into such sharp focus. It&#39;s very British, I think.”</p><p> <strong>Holman:</strong> “It&#39;s just like, say what you see. I always say to people when they&#39;re struggling with writer&#39;s block, &#39;You don&#39;t have to have something amazing to write about. Just write about what&#39;s in front of you&#39;.”</p><p> <strong>And, of course, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/seal-kate-nash-soft-play-and-more-announced-as-special-guests-for-robbie-williams-london-bst-hyde-park-2024-3767743">you were both on the bill for Robbie Williams&#39; big Hyde Park show</a> last summer…</strong></p><p> <strong>Vincent:</strong> “Obviously Robbie gets it – he&#39;s the link! We went backstage [to talk to him] as he was getting pampered. Someone&#39;s hands were coming in and creaming him and brushing his hair as he was talking to us. To him, it was the most normal thing in the world but me and Isaac were just like… what&#39;s happening?! Danny Dyer was also there watching the England game on the TV. It was fucking bizarre.” </p><figure id="attachment_3847199" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3847199" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3847199" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayinterview-copy-photo.jpg" alt="Soft Play performing live on stage" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayinterview-copy-photo.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayinterview-copy-photo-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayinterview-copy-photo-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayinterview-copy-photo-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayinterview-copy-photo-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/SoftPlayinterview-copy-photo-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3847199" class="wp-caption-text"> Soft Play perform live. CREDIT: Stuart Westwood/SOPA Images/LightRocket/Getty</figcaption></figure><p> <strong>What did you make of the recent artist-led protest to the proposed use of musician&#39;s catalogues to train <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/ai">AI</a> , where <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/damon-albarn-kate-bush-annie-lennox-over-1000-artists-release-silent-album-protest-uk-copyright-ai-laws-3841081">more than 1,000 musicians released a collective silent album</a> ? Is AI something that feels like a threat, creatively?</strong></p><p> <strong>Vincent:</strong> “It&#39;s scary for the people that are sitting on fucking towers of cash, but it doesn&#39;t even matter if someone rips us off on AI – we&#39;re not big streamers anyway. And maybe that&#39;s a bit apathetic but we&#39;ve got bigger things to worry about than AI as musicians. The disparity in the music industry is so huge now – we&#39;re a two-piece band that can sell out a whole tour and we&#39;re still struggling to make ends meet.”</p><p> <strong>Nash:</strong> “[The argument is] &#39;make it fair&#39;, but I need a bit more detail than a silent album on <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/spotify">Spotify</a> – one of the most exploitative platforms in the whole industry. Make it fair for who? And exactly which body or organisation are you asking to discuss the terms and conditions of exactly what makes it fair? Because if it&#39;s the major labels, I think we all know how that&#39;s gonna go.</p><p> “I think there&#39;s a big focus on AI as posing a threat to human-made art and I don&#39;t think there is a threat to human-made art. This is probably how people felt when hip-hop culture and the birth of sampling happened. Things already aren&#39;t fair, so can we actually deal with what&#39;s happening now?”</p><p> <strong>Vincent:</strong> “Ultimately, I guess Spotify will benefit from AI music because people will just keep streaming, and if they&#39;re not having to pay people because it&#39;s AI then it&#39;s just gonna water down what normal musicians are making.”</p><p> <strong>Nash:</strong> “I do think music has value but it&#39;s only going to a couple of people. The industry has taught people that it&#39;s valueless, but look at the gaming industry – it&#39;s booming.”</p><p> <strong>Vincent:</strong> “You have to buy games, why don&#39;t you have to buy music? I&#39;ve always said that me and Isaac should do an OnlyFans like you Kate, but then we were worried that it would look gimmicky. We could just do really soft content…”</p><p> <strong>Nash:</strong> “Oh my god, you actually should!” </p><figure id="attachment_3847203" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3847203" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3847203" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/KateNashinterview-copy-picture.jpg" alt="Kate Nash performing live on stage" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/KateNashinterview-copy-picture.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/KateNashinterview-copy-picture-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/KateNashinterview-copy-picture-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/KateNashinterview-copy-picture-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/KateNashinterview-copy-picture-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/KateNashinterview-copy-picture-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3847203" class="wp-caption-text"> Kate Nash performs live. CREDIT: Andrew Benge/Redferns/Getty</figcaption></figure><p> <strong>How is the OnlyFans going, Kate?</strong></p><p> <strong>Nash:</strong> “What&#39;s crazy is you realise how few people you need [to subscribe] to make really decent money. They take 20 per cent and I take 80 per cent, and I&#39;m making more from that than my music even though I&#39;ve got way more fans with music. It&#39;s not just that sex sells – music also makes people loads of money, and if we were getting paid fairly and things were getting split properly, I would be making loads. &#39;Foundations&#39; has over 100million streams – not to sound like a dickhead, but why aren&#39;t I a millionaire?”</p><p> <strong>Isaac and Laurie, you&#39;ve <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/soft-play-share-emotive-new-single-everything-and-nothing-listen-3762500">been open about the mental health struggles</a> that touring life has had on you in the past. What did you think of <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/chappell-roan-responds-to-op-ed-criticising-grammys-speech-they-best-put-their-money-where-their-mouth-is-otherwise-move-out-of-the-way-3836413">Chappell Roan&#39;s Grammy speech about artist care</a> , and how are you balancing it all these days?</strong></p><p> <strong>Vincent:</strong> “Every week you see a superstar postponing their tour – <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lola-young">Lola Young</a> just did it, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/arlo-parks-cancels-us-tour-dates-due-to-debilitating-mental-health-issues-3311930">Arlo Parks did it</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-cancels-upcoming-us-tour-dates-to-look-after-my-own-mental-health-3308481">Sam Fender does it</a> . The model is broken but everyone that gets paid off your back wants you out on the road because that&#39;s where the money&#39;s coming from. Me and Isaac are broken from our last tour and we can&#39;t take days off &#39;cause it&#39;s too expensive, so you&#39;re just stuck between a rock and a hard place.</p><p> “God bless <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/chappell-roan">Chappell Roan</a> . I fucking rate what she does and I love how she&#39;s speaking out about stuff, even just <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/chappell-roan-writes-to-superfans-about-predatory-behaviour-women-dont-owe-you-shit-3786492">about how people don&#39;t own her</a> . These conversations need to be had. I was in an airport recently and my kids were screaming, one of them&#39;s nearly getting trapped in an escalator and someone asked me for a selfie and I just couldn&#39;t do it. And I felt awful about it for weeks.”</p><p> <strong>Nash:</strong> “I once got asked for a selfie in the nursing home my grandad was dying in, in front of my grandad. And I took it, and he&#39;s literally in the background, dying, hardly able to breathe.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Slaves, &#039;Consume Or Be Consumed&#039; - NME Song Stories" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zopcj7E820Q?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> <strong>Isaac, you recently opened up about your incredibly traumatic experience of losing a baby [ <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/soft-play-isaac-holman-to-run-charity-ultramarathon-after-loss-of-baby-3827549#:~:text=make%20a%20difference%E2%80%9D-,Soft%20Play's%20Isaac%20Holman%20to%20run%20charity%20ultramarathon%20after%20loss,money%20to%20make%20a%20difference%E2%80%9D&amp;text=Soft%20Play's%20Isaac%20Holman,his%20and%20his%20wife's%20baby.">Isaac is running an ultramarathon in support of Abigail&#39;s Charity</a> – <a href="https://www.justgiving.com/page/isaac-holman-1735922719076?utm_medium=FR&amp;utm_source=CL&amp;fbclid=PAZXh0bgNhZW0CMTEAAaaHTQMHKqkGAUAxkWKhfSleX_aB1su4EiNsQrxGCmRLmHyAz6tPzO9lIyo_aem_NGeV_IEXNsYVmfoLeVv5lg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">donate here</a> ]. Did you feel supported by the industry in being able to take time to grieve?</strong></p><p> <strong>Holman:</strong> “It was fortunate that it happened during the time that we&#39;d just come off tour, but it doesn&#39;t really stop. I wasn&#39;t ready to go back to work when we toured Australia and I had a terrible time. I didn&#39;t sleep and I was really ill and my mental health was terrible. I was really in the depths of it and we had to go and work and I found it really fucking difficult; I&#39;m still a little bit traumatised from it.</p><p> “We&#39;re going on tour in America in April and I&#39;m already shitting it, but that&#39;s just the way it is. When I&#39;m in a bad place, the touring isn&#39;t sustainable and I don&#39;t know how to [manage it]. It&#39;s not like we&#39;re just getting on stage and having a little sing song, it&#39;s so fucking exhausting. When I&#39;m with Laurie, we&#39;re super open and vulnerable with each other and that helps – just being able to go off in the daytime and talk things through. But you can totally see why people just completely fucking lose it.”</p><p> <strong>There&#39;s a lot of bleakness but it also feels, as you say, like there&#39;s something of a sea change happening with how transparent artists are being about these struggles…</strong></p><p> <strong>Nash:</strong> “That&#39;s so powerful, and there&#39;s no shame in it. If musicians could realise that there&#39;s a lot of power in being open and transparent and coming together… Can you imagine if we had a festival line-up and we knew what everyone was being paid? We&#39;d be able to see that women aren&#39;t being paid as much, or the budgets are different for different artists – I think we should know shit like that. The industry benefits from us feeling like we have to behave and hide anything that isn&#39;t completely shiny, but it&#39;s not a shiny job.”</p><p> <em>Soft Play release &#39;Heavier Jelly&#39; on April 18. They hit the road this spring for a run of North American dates, including <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/coachella-2025-lady-gaga-green-day-post-malone-travis-scott-lead-line-up-3814558">Coachella 2025</a> . This summer, the band <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/idles-confirm-special-guests-for-bristol-block-party-the-voidz-soft-play-more-3843737#:~:text=IDLES%20have%20announced%20the%20special,two%2Dnight%20festival%20in%20August.&amp;text=In%20November%2C%20the%20punk%20band,site%20in%20over%20two%20decades.">open for IDLES in Bristol</a> , support <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-libertines">The Libertines</a> in Margate and play <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/reading-leeds-2025-limp-bizkit-d-block-europe-heartworms-and-nell-mescal-lead-huge-line-up-additions-3842012#:~:text=Reading%20%26%20Leeds%20has%20announced%20a,out%20the%20updated%20bill%20below.&amp;text=This%20year's%20edition%20of%20the,between%20August%2021%20and%2024.">Reading &amp; Leeds 2025</a> .</em></p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/soft-play-and-kate-nash-tell-us-about-their-playful-and-very-british-new-collab-slushy-3846797">Soft Play and Kate Nash tell us about their playful and “very British” new collab &#39;Slushy&#39;</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
这是2025年Iheartradio Music Awards的所有获奖者https://www.nme.com/news/music/here-are-all-the-winners-from-the-iheartradio-music-awards-2025-3847188?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=here-are-all-the-winners-from-the-iheartradio-music-awards-2025Liberty Dunworth Tue, 18 Mar 2025 13:24:10 +0000 Music NewsNewsAlternativeDanceElectronicHip-hopIndiePopRapRock https://www.nme.com/?p=3847188 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="FINNEAS and Billie Eilish accept the Album of the Year Award onstage at the 2025 iHeartRadio Music Awards" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Among the big winners on the night were Benson Boone, Taylor Swift and Gracie Abrams</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/here-are-all-the-winners-from-the-iheartradio-music-awards-2025-3847188">Here are all the winners from the iHeartRadio Music Awards 2025</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="FINNEAS and Billie Eilish accept the Album of the Year Award onstage at the 2025 iHeartRadio Music Awards" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/eilish@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/benson-boone">Benson Boone</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/taylor-swift">Taylor Swift</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/gracie-abrams">Gracie Abrams</a> are among the big names taking home trophies at the 2025 edition of the iHeartRadio Music Awards. Find a full list of winners below.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/taylor-swift-eras-tour-end-impact-3820896">Taylor Swift&#39;s Eras Tour comes to an end: a look at its massive global impact</a></strong></li></ul><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/iheartradio-music-awards-2025-taylor-swift-and-morgan-wallen-lead-nominations-3831256">This year&#39;s edition of the awards ceremony</a> took place last night (March 17) at the Dolby Theatre in Los Angeles, and saw countless artists take home wins for their huge hit singles and albums from across the past 12 months.</p><p> Among the winners was <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lady-gaga">Lady Gaga</a> , who took home the prestigious Innovator Award on the night and used her speech to both <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/lady-gaga-hits-back-ageism-in-pop-im-just-getting-warmed-up-3847136">call out “ageism” in the pop music industry</a> and reassure fans that she is only just getting started in her career.</p><p> Another memorable moment on the night came from Benson Boone, who swept up the award in the Song Of The Year category with his massive hit &#39;Beautiful Things&#39;. Not only did it see him take home an award after <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grammys-2025-see-the-full-list-of-winners-3833854">going home empty-handed at the Grammys</a> , but also marked the first male artist to win in the category since 2021, when <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-weeknd">The Weeknd</a> took home the award for his song &#39;Blinding Lights&#39; (via <a href="https://www.billboard.com/music/awards/2025-iheartradio-music-awards-winners-list-1235924293/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Billboard</em></a> ).</p><p> Elsewhere, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/mariah-carey">Mariah Carey</a> took home the Icon Award, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nelly">Nelly</a> took home the Landmark Award and Gracie Abrams nabbed the Breakthrough Award. For the latter, she used her acceptance speech to share her love of Taylor Swift, <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/olivia-rodrigo">Olivia Rodrigo</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/noah-kahan">Noah Kahan</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-national">The National</a> . </p><figure id="attachment_3847143" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3847143" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3847143" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/lady-gaga@2000x1270-2.jpg" alt="Lady Gaga accepts the Innovator Award onstage at the 2025 iHeartRadio Music Awards" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/lady-gaga@2000x1270-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/lady-gaga@2000x1270-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/lady-gaga@2000x1270-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/lady-gaga@2000x1270-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/lady-gaga@2000x1270-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/lady-gaga@2000x1270-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3847143" class="wp-caption-text"> Lady Gaga accepts the Innovator Award onstage at the 2025 iHeartRadio Music Awards. CREDIT: Kevin Winter/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a> took home the award for Album Of The Year for &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/billie-eilish-hit-me-hard-and-soft-review-tracklist-lyrics-3756826">Hit Me Hard And Soft</a> &#39; – beating off competition from <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/beyonce">Beyoncé</a> &#39;s &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/beyonce-cowboy-carter-album-review-tracklist-lyrics-3611699">Cowboy Carter</a> &#39;, after <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grammys-2025-see-the-full-list-of-winners-3833854">losing out to the country record at the Grammys in the same category</a> .</p><p> The biggest winner on the night, however, was Taylor Swift. She took home nine awards including <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/taylor-swift-shares-unseen-mirrorball-performance-after-winning-tour-of-the-century-prize-at-iheartradio-music-awards-2025-3847109#:~:text=Music%20Awards%202025-,Taylor%20Swift%20shares%20unseen%20'Mirrorball'%20performance%20after%20winning%20Tour%20Of,at%20iHeartRadio%20Music%20Awards%202025&amp;text=Taylor%20Swift%20has%20shared%20a,the%20iHeartRadio%20Music%20Awards%202025.">Tour Of The Century for her massive run of &#39;Eras&#39; dates</a> , as well as Best Music Video, Best Lyrics, Favourite Surprise Guest, Artist Of The Year and more.</p><p> Other big winners on the night included <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/post-malone">Post Malone</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sabrina-carpenter">Sabrina Carpenter</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/shinedown">Shinedown</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/charli-xcx">Charli XCX</a> . Find a full list below.</p><h2> <strong>The 2025 iHeart Radio Award